div.p:
"That is not true, my lord. You would have it sent you by the carrier from London;
                  or, had you wanted it from us, would have despatched a servant to obtain it. You
                  have some other motive for this extraordinary visit."

"Pray, answer for yourself, sir," she cried, gaily. "I intend to play with spirit;
                  that is, if I have a Frederick who will make love to me properly—on the stage—as
                  he is in duty bound to do."
